article.description: — Allin Blunt had a career-high 23 points as UMass Lowell beat Maine 71-62 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Blunt scores 23 to lead UMass Lowell over Maine 71-62
article.linkText: Blunt scores 23 to lead UMass Lowell over Maine 71-62
article.story: LOWELL, Mass. -- — Allin Blunt had a career-high 23 points as UMass Lowell beat Maine 71-62 on Wednesday night. Blunt made 4 of 6 3-pointers. Kalil Thomas had 13 points and six rebounds for UMass Lowell (10-7, 2/3 America East Conference). Justin Faison added 11 points. Max Brooks had 7 points and five blocks. Kristians Feierbergs scored a season-high 22 points and had 11 rebounds for the Black Bears (3-12, 0-4), who have now lost six straight games. Maks Klanjscek added 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
